Just landed back in NYC and honestly these last 12 days went by way to fast… but nevertheless my heart is so grateful and happy that I got to spend some time in my beautiful home country and see my favourite people in South Africa 🇿🇦 

Now time to end this year in a high and get ready for what the new year holds 🫶🏼

This year… 

2022 you’ve seen so many versions of me that I never knew existed, you’ve seen me at my lowest yet you’ve seen me slowly make my way up. You’ve seen me in love, heartbroken, emotionless, scared and fragile yet you’ve seen me pick myself up and rebuild my trust in people and the meaning of love. You’ve seen me cry my eyes out yet you’ve seen my most pure smile and witnessed me laughing till my stomach hurt. You’ve been there for every sleepless night as well as every small victory. You know my journey inside out and probably judge some of the dump choices I’ve made this year. You’ve taught me strength and forced me to learn some painful lessons along the way. You’ve helped me realise my worth once more and opened up some doors I thought where locked forever. 

2022 you’ve been challenging been sometimes cruel to say the least but you’ve also been so forgiving and amazing at the same time. 

Not gonna lie, I’m childlike excited to see what challenges and amazing new beginnings 2023 will have for me 🫶🏼

and with that the 2022 season comes to and end 🥂

Happy new year #2023

social_posts.post_text:
If redoing this trip meant: 
- 3:30 am alarms
- extreme heat with no air conditioning 
- no wifi & barely any signal 
- no warm water 
- no English speaking people near me
- the same food for a week at every meal of the day
- dust and ants everywhere 
- living in a little hut with the bare necessities 
- 4 flights and a 6 hours off road drives
- 7 hour layovers 
- the friendliest locals 
- the best crew to work with ( thank @maaji ) 
- making new friends and the best roommate 
- hours alone in the middle of nowhere 

I’d HAPPILY do it all over again tomorrow 🫶🏼 

Not gonna lie, I’m returning to the states a little sad to leave this place behind 🇨🇴

March… thank you for allowing me to fall in love with MYSELF 🤍 

My March madness was filled with: 
- 5 countries in 4 weeks 
- a lot of alone time & self reflection 
- filled with laughter, friends & love 
- amazing work opportunities 
- very very little sleep 
- learning new creative skills 
- way to little studying ( I am indeed behind now) 
- amazing food 
- countless hours in the air & in cars 
- no routine whatsoever 
- some tears 
- beautiful sunsets & puppy love 

March, you left me exhausted emotionally, physically and mentally and I wouldn’t have it any other way. Thank you, I can’t wait to see what April holds. 🤍

🇿🇦 South Africa Part 1 : 
Okay, so this trip totally unlocked this one huge truth: Cape Town, South Africa? Man, there’s just no other spot in this world like it! I mean, seriously, the vibe, the food, the crazy mix of cultures, the wild nature, those epic sunsets - it’s a whole vibe!

And let’s talk about the people - they’re like a warm hug wrapped in kindness! These little things, they’re Cape Town’s secret sauce. 

Even though i’m not currently calling it my place of residence, I feel so extremely grateful and stoked to always claim it as my “home” the place I’m from, the place that saw me grow up, gave me my character & even my accent. Growing up there? Total gift! Now, having this place to bounce back to? Priceless!

🇿🇦 South Africa part 2: 
It’s my last 24 hours here at home in South Africa, and man, these waves of sadness and anxiety keeps hitting me out of the blue. Tomorrow, on Christmas Day, I’m jetting back to America where I’m currently working and living. I’ve been so lucky to soak up three amazing weeks here, surrounded by friends and family. Yet, tomorrow evening, I’ll be across the ocean, gearing up to celebrate someone very special in my life on their birthday.

Yes, I am the one who made the call to leave South Africa on Christmas Day in order to make it in time for their big day on the 26th. Even though I’m psyched to reunite and celebrate with them, it’s still a gut-wrenching feeling to bid farewell to my loved ones here.

Today, I found myself tearing up for no apparent reason. I tried to play it cool, shrugged it off with a laugh, and asked my mom, ‘Why am I even crying?’ Her response hit deep, ‘It’s okay, sweetie. You’re allowed to be emotional, your heart is split between two places.’

So, I guess it’s okay for me to feel this crazy mix of excitement and fear for the unknown topped with a big ol’ dollop of sadness all at once, right? 

🤍

🇿🇦 Bye for now South Africa 
Finally, the paramount reason for my visit back home: FAMILY! Words fail to express my gratitude for our tight-knit bond, the unwavering support, and boundless love we share. Through every moment—laughter, tears, and all in between—my heart brims with joy for having them. As I bid farewell at the airport, tears stream down, not of sorrow but of sheer happiness, of immense gratitude! See again soon, I cherish and adore each one of you. Love you ♥️

Oh, and a Merry Christmas from my family to yours!

That’s a wrap on 2023… 
Oh what a rollercoaster of a year it has been, can’t wait to see what 2024 holds. Manifesting tons of fun, work, travel, love & happiness ✨
